author: AAP
title: Shark who mauled bodyboarder a great white
summary: BIOLOGISTS believe the shark that attacked a bodyboarder at Lighthouse Beach Port Macquarie over the weekend was a 2.7m great white.

author: By Evan Schwarten
title: Fortescue banks on Chinese stimulus
summary: FORTESCUE Metals expects China's stimulus efforts to help boost demand for iron ore following an 88 per cent slide in its full year profit.

author: AAP
title: No assault charge for NSW Labor boss
summary: POLICE have declined to charge NSW Labor's most senior official Jamie Clements over an alleged assault on a parliamentary staffer in parliament.

author: By Karlis Salna
title: Monis 'never seen at any Sydney mosques'
summary: THE inquest into the Sydney siege has heard that claims by gunman Man Haron Monis about his standing in the Muslim community were likely to be false.

author: AAP
title: New SA plant may employ Holden workers
summary: A NEW food processing plant may be built in Adelaide's north and could eventually provide jobs for Holden workers looking for work over the next few years.

author: AAP
title: Heydon delays ruling on standing aside
summary: A DECISION on whether unions royal commissioner Dyson Heydon stands aside won't be delivered on Tuesday.

author: AAP
title: Masterchef judge sued for unpaid bills
summary: MASTERCHEF judge Gary Mehigan is being sued for more than $167000 over unpaid invoices for building a Melbourne events venue.

author: AAP
title: SA premier defends minister's travel
summary: SOUTH Australian Premier Jay Weatherill has defended his tourism minister against criticism of his travel spending.

author: Simone Ziaziaris
title: No subsidy for Meningococcal B vaccine
summary: PARENTS who wish to vaccinate their child against meningococcal B will be faced with a pricey bill after it was rejected by the government's PBAC.

author: By Annette Blackwell
title: Pope Francis has 'not' shown leadership
summary: RETIRED bishop Geoffrey Robinson has told a royal commission that papal leadership on combating the abuse of minors has never been up to scratch.
